 Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology/Management
Information Systems (or equivalent) from an accredited college or university;
 Minimum seven (7) years software development experience (in multiple environments) employing formal software development methodologies;
 Minimum of three (3) years of in-depth core applications work experience in
Utility Customer Information Systems (CIS).

